<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The Zend/Locale/Data/ directory contains a number of codeset variants, such as sr_Latn.xml. (Serbian is by default cyrillic).</p>

<p>(1) These variants cannot be used as they are not listed in Zend_Locale::$_localeData[]</p>

<p>(2) I am reliably informed (<a href="http://www.openi18n.org/docs/text/LocNameGuide-V10.txt">http://openi18n.org/docs/text/â€¦</a>) that the correct naming convention for these locales is "sr@latin"</p>

<p>To fix this, I propose</p>

<p>(a) these codeset variants are added to the array</p>

<p>(b) Zend_Locale accepts @latin, @cyrillic, etc. as synonyms for _Latn, _Cyrl, etc.</p>

